contents.desc: Everyone has a hidden side of themselves they don‚Äôt want to reveal. This is why I create art‚Äîbecause few things feel as sincere as the marks made on a piece of paper.

I stand tall. I create with courage and compassion. I work hard to prove to myself that I‚Äôm stronger than what once sought to define me. Vulnerability is a source of strength, yet I am afraid of it being misconstrued as a desire for attention.

Self doubt cuts deep. Inadequacy and comparison feels like an addiction. Old wounds follow me no matter how far I run. Inevitably, I end up back in the same place, feeling as helpless as I did years ago.
They say it‚Äôs time to let go ‚Äî but how do I even begin to love myself?
